☁️ Azure Blob Storage Resources
Storage Account
- Unique namespace for all your data.
- Example endpoint: http://mystorageaccount.blob.core.windows.net

Container
- Organizes blobs (like directories in a file system).
- Unlimited number of containers in a storage account.
- Container name rules:
  - 3-63 characters long.
  - Only lowercase letters, numbers, and dashes (-).
  - Cannot have consecutive dashes.
- Example container URI: https://myaccount.blob.core.windows.net/mycontainer

Blob
- Types of blobs:
  - Block Blobs: Store text and binary data (up to 190.7 TiB).
  - Append Blobs: Optimized for append operations (e.g., logging).
  - Page Blobs: Store random access files (up to 8 TB), used for Azure VM disks.
- Example blob URI: https://myaccount.blob.core.windows.net/mycontainer/myblob

